<p>With that being said, short cut keys have a huge role in the 21st century in building a proffesional carrer and help out in daily lives. It makes a work more efficient, easier and less time consuming. Using shortcut keys can stand out one from another during competitive exams or job interviews leading to academic or professional success</p>
<h1><b>Some important shortcur keys are:</b></h1>
<div class="container">
<pre>
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+a</kbd> to select all
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+b</kbd> to bold text
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+c</kbd> to copy
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+e</kbd> to align text to center
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+i</kbd> to make text ilatilc
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+j</kbd> to justify
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+l</kbd> to align text to left
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+m</kbd> to minimize window
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+p</kbd> to create pdf
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+r</kbd> to reload/align text to right
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+t</kbd> to open new tab
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+v</kbd> to paste
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+w</kbd> to close tab
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+x</kbd> to cut
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+z</kbd> to undo
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+shift+n</kbd> to crate new folder
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+shift+delete</kbd> to delete all browsing history
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+shift+o</kbd> to open bookmarks manager
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+plus(+)</kbd> to zoom in
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+minus(-)</kbd> to zoom out
    <kbd>ctrl/cmd+0</kbd> to reset zoom
</pre><hr>
</div>
<p>Powerpoint is a very necessary skill for presenting any thought or idea in a presentable manner in a formal way. Wether it is in school,college,university or in workplace, making a powerpoint is a must in all cases. So here are some simple powerpoint tricks for excelling you powerpoint presentations</p>
<h1><b>Powerpoint tricks:</b></h1>
<div class="container">
<ul>
    <li>Press <kbd>ctrl/cmd+d</kbd> to dupicate any object, slide,image,text box etc</li>
    <li>Press <kbd>b</kbd> to have a black screen durin>g presentation</li>
    <li>Press <kbd>W</kbd> to have a white screen durin>g presentation</li>
    <li>Press <kbd>slide number+enter</kbd> to directlt move to a speciifc slide during presentation</li>
    <li>Press <kbd>ctrl/cmd+g</kbd> to group objects</li>
    <li>Press <kbd>ctrl/cmd+shit+g</kbd> to ungroup objects</li>
    <li>For a gradient background: press<code> design > format background > gradient fill</code></li>
    <li> to insert picture in a specific shape press:<code> insert > shapes/icons > shape format > picture fill > insert picture</code></li>
</ul>
</div>
